From: Pavel Tikhomirov <ptikhomirov@virtuozzo.com>
Date: Thu, 11 Jan 2024 23:06:39 +0800
Subject: netfilter: propagate net to nf_bridge_get_physindev
Git-commit: a54e72197037d2c9bfcd70dddaac8c8ccb5b41ba
Patch-mainline: v6.8-rc1
References: CVE-2024-35839 bsc#1224726

This is a preparation patch for replacing physindev with physinif on
nf_bridge_info structure. We will use dev_get_by_index_rcu to resolve
device, when needed, and it requires net to be available.

Signed-off-by: Pavel Tikhomirov <ptikhomirov@virtuozzo.com>
Reviewed-by: Simon Horman <horms@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Pablo Neira Ayuso <pablo@netfilter.org>
Acked-by: Fernando Fernandez Mancera <fmancera@suse.de>
---
 include/linux/netfilter_bridge.h           |    2 +-
 include/net/netfilter/nf_log.h             |    3 ++-
 net/ipv4/netfilter/nf_log_arp.c            |    2 +-
 net/ipv4/netfilter/nf_log_ipv4.c           |    2 +-
 net/ipv4/netfilter/nf_reject_ipv4.c        |    2 +-
 net/ipv6/netfilter/nf_log_ipv6.c           |    2 +-
